text: <!channel> does anyone have their jawbone up charger here that i could borrow?
marissa handed me hers from across our desks!
but thank you trent! i may take you up on yours at a later date
my up band is toast so i’m not really using the charger anymore
My Up-Band is available for someone else to use it. Not using mine anymore. Could bring it in tomorrow or next week.
I know I’m enjoying freedom from the shackles, I’m good over here

I’ll also mention that I’m only starting to reuse my Jawbone so that I can more effectively test the builds and get real data associated with my user, and it would be helpful to have as many of those real ‘test’ users as possible. :slightly_smiling_face:
yeah that has been nagging me a bit already now that i’m starting to get these builds, maybe melissa and felix should bring those in and i’ll reconsider
is anyone else’s compass slack rendering in helvetica? it’s freakin me out
if it is desired i am totally happy to wear it again. sharing data if it helps. just let me know.
yea it would be great! we’ll make sure the team gets a new iOS build soon, then if you’ve been wearing your jawbone and connect it to the app that’d be rad
I’m happy to adopt a band for data’s/beta’s sake

thanks james! sounds like we’ll all be getting a new iOS build early next week, which would be the right time to grab a jawbone and hook it up. if anyone is an android + jawbone user, they can do so now.
